==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Purblind
<hw>Pur"blind`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[For
<ets>pure-blind</ets>, i. e., wholly blind. See <er>Pure</er>, and cf.
<er>Poreblind</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Wholly blind.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Purblind</xex> Argus, all eyes and no sight.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Nearsighted, or dim-sighted; seeing obscurely;
<as>as, a <ex>purblind</ex> eye; a <ex>purblind</ex>
mole.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The saints have not so sharp eyes to see down from heaven; they be
<qex>purblind</qex>and sand-blind.</q> <rj><qau>Latimer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>O <qex>purblind</qex> race of miserable men.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Pur"blind`ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Pur"blind`ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Purcelane</ent>⟦br⟧
